Title : Ethan Becker
Text : {{for|the author and speech coach|Ethan F. Becker}}
'''Ethan Becker''' American Knife Maker. He is the son of Marion and John William Becker and grandson of [[Irma S. Rombauer|Irma Starkloff Rombauer]], the original author of [[The Joy of Cooking]]. Ethan studied at [[Le Cordon Bleu|Cordon Bleu]] in [[Paris]] in 1971 and "was entrusted with" authorship of "Joy" in 1976 from his mother.<ref name="thejoykitchen">{{cite web|url=http://www.thejoykitchen.com/all-about-joy/ethan-becker|title=Ethan Becker &#124; The Joy of Cooking|publisher=thejoykitchen.com|accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

In the 1980s he founded [[Becker Knife and Tool]] which in time partnered with BlackJack Knives. Becker Knife and Tool later partnered with [[Camillus Cutlery Company]] (until Camillus' bankruptcy in 2007) to produce Ethan's knife designs which are currently produced by [[Ka-Bar]] Knives and manufactured in the USA.<ref name="kabar">{{cite web|url=http://www.kabar.com/knives/us-made|title=KA-BAR Knives, Inc. - U.S. Made - Hardcore Lives. Hardcore Knives.|publisher=kabar.com|accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

Ethan is also the creator of the "Becker Patrol Pack"  manufactured by Eagle Industries,<ref name="eagleindustries">{{cite web|url=http://www.eagleindustries.com/products/detail.aspx?id=9|title=Eagle Industries - Product Details|publisher=eagleindustries.com|accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref> the CMI Figure 8 Descender and other climbing gear.<ref name="thejoykitchen"/>

